: The answer is disorganized and jumps between different points without a clear timeline. It is difficult for the interviewer to grasp the sequence of events. Depth check: Good: The candidate provides specific details about the disagreement and the logic behind their actions. They include a reflection on what was learned from the experience. Mid: The candidate gives a general overview of the event but misses the nuances of the interaction. There is very little reflection on how this experience shaped their future work. Bad: The candidate provides a very brief response that lacks any detail or context. It feels like a generic answer that could apply to almost any situation. Clarity check: Good: The candidate uses simple and effective language to explain a complex interpersonal dynamic. Their communication is professional and keeps the listener engaged throughout. Mid: The candidate uses some filler words or repetitive phrases that detract from the overall message. The story is understandable but requires extra effort from the listener to piece together. Bad: The candidate is unable to articulate their thoughts clearly and often loses their train of thought. The language used is unprofessional or confusing. Relevance to role: Good: The candidate demonstrates the high level of collaboration required for the job. They show they can handle the inevitable friction that comes with team-based work. Mid: The candidate shows they are capable of working in a team but might need guidance when conflicts arise. They meet the basic requirements for cooperation but are not a standout. Bad: The candidate’s response suggests they might be difficult to work with or lack the maturity for a team environment. They do not demonstrate the interpersonal awareness needed for the project.|1|Tell me about a time when you had a disagreement with a teammate over how to complete a project task?|PASS|98|[\"Strict adherence to rubric structure with per-section Good/Mid/Bad labels.\", \"Questions are well-formatted, single-sentence interrogatives.\", \"Excellent differentiation between Good, Mid, and Bad example answers.\", \"High level of detail and relevance across all competencies.\"]|587130c33cd5bb6372e4988375795256f0f22138|d06650cf7f058a41ecd0b8dc33cf0c4886e8f503|Software Developer|20|1db4a2612ce41bf150139064e08c85a4ff5a6035|gemini-3-flash-preview|1.0|2026-02-20T16:39:17.255482Z
