 understand the 'why' behind the 'how'. Mid: The candidate provides only the most basic steps of the process. They miss out on the quality assurance aspects like testing or syncing. Bad: The response is extremely shallow and shows a lack of experience with professional workflows. There is no mention of any standard tools or practices. Clarity check: Good: The explanation is technical yet accessible and easy to follow. The candidate uses industry-standard terminology correctly. Mid: The candidate uses informal language that is somewhat imprecise. While the message gets across, it lacks professional polish. Bad: The candidate is unable to describe the process in a way that makes sense. Their lack of clarity suggests a lack of familiarity with the task. Relevance to role: Good: The candidate is ready to contribute to a shared codebase immediately. They follow the practices that keep a project running smoothly. Mid: The candidate would need some initial training on the team's specific workflow. They have the basic knowledge but need to be more disciplined. Bad: The candidate lacks the fundamental skills required for the technical side of the job. Their current approach would be a hindrance to the team.|3|Explain the step-by-step process you follow when you need to submit your code changes to a shared repository?|PASS|98|[\"Strict adherence to rubric structure with per-section Good/Mid/Bad labels.\", \"Questions are well-formatted, single-sentence interrogatives.\", \"Excellent differentiation between Good, Mid, and Bad example answers.\", \"High level of detail and relevance across all competencies.\"]|587130c33cd5bb6372e4988375795256f0f22138|d06650cf7f058a41ecd0b8dc33cf0c4886e8f503|Software Developer|22|1db4a2612ce41bf150139064e08c85a4ff5a6035|gemini-3-flash-preview|1.0|2026-02-20T16:39:17.255482Z
